      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ تَلَقِّي اَلْغَنَمِ فَقَالَ \"لاَ تَلَقَّ وَ لاَ تَشْتَرِ مَا تُلُقِّيَ وَ لاَ تَأْكُلْ مِنْ لَحْمِ مَا تُلُقِّيَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3989 - It is narrated from Minhal al-Qassab who said: I asked Abu Abdullah (as) about intercepting sheep.\nImam (as) said: \"Do not intercept, do not buy what has been intercepted, and do not eat the meat of what has been intercepted.\""
        ]
      }
    },
